# Testing (EARS-driven)

- Each acceptance criterion is written in EARS and gets at least one test. Name the test after
  the criterion id, e.g. `it('EARS-OUV-03: when ICP passes, generates OUV-#### consecutivo')`.
- EARS forms to expect in specs: Ubiquitous ("The system shall…"), Event ("When <trigger>,
  the system shall…"), State ("While <state>, the system shall…"), Unwanted ("If <condition>,
  then the system shall…"), Optional ("Where <segment>, the system shall…").
- Backend: unit-test services (business rules) + contract-test controllers (status, shape,
  auth). Use an in-memory/throwaway MySQL schema or transactional rollback per test.
- State machines (LEAD, OUV, PRE, SER, PRICING, FACTURA): test every allowed transition AND
  at least one forbidden transition.
- Workflows WF001–WF016: test trigger → condition → action, including audit_log write.
- Frontend: test rendering + interaction of shared components; mock the API.
- A module is "% complete" = passing EARS criteria ÷ total EARS criteria for that module.
